---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Sound Design" active="sound-design">
  <div class="container">

    <section class="page-header">
      <h3>Tonal Palette</h3>
      <h1>Sound Design</h1>
      <p>Outboard gear, amp sims, effects, and software plugins. The tools that shape the sound at every stage.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="vu-bar" style="background: rgba(168,90,74,0.35)"></div>

    <section class="ruled">
      <h3>Outboard Character</h3>
      <div class="grid-2 mt-sm">
        <div class="card">
          <span class="card__label">Preamp / EQ</span>
          <h4>HA73-EQX2</h4>
          <p>Neve 1073 style. Two channels of transformer-coupled warmth with 3-band EQ. Adds harmonic richness and weight that digital preamps can't replicate. The foundation of every recording's tone.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="card__label">FET Compressor</span>
          <h4>WA76-D2</h4>
          <p>1176 style. Fast attack, program-dependent release. Catches transients and adds that distinctive FET bite. Two channels &mdash; one for vocal, one for guitar. The workhorse.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="card__label">Optical Leveling</span>
          <h4>Audioscape Opto</h4>
          <p>LA-2A style. Slow, smooth optical compression that gently rides the level without squashing dynamics. Sits at the end of the vocal chain where it evens everything out.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="card__label">Versatile Compression</span>
          <h4>Distressor</h4>
          <p>Does everything. Gentle leveling, aggressive limiting, harmonic distortion modes. Sits at the end of the guitar chain where it adds character that changes with how hard you play.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ruled">
      <h3>Guitar Amp Sims</h3>
      <div class="prose mt-sm">
        <p>
          The Wing's built-in amp sims run on dedicated buses before the outboard chain. Three presets cover the range: a Mesa-style lead with dark, controlled gain; a Fender-style clean with bright sparkle; and a transparent acoustic preset for piezo DIs. Switching is instant &mdash; mute one bus, unmute another.
        </p>
        <p>
          During playback, the same amp sims process recorded tracks. A rhythm guitar recorded clean can be re-amped through the Mesa sim and the full outboard chain, giving a completely different character to the same performance.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ruled">
      <h3>Wing Effects</h3>
      <div class="prose mt-sm">
        <p>
          The Wing carries 16 effect slots with models ranging from classic reverbs (plate, hall, spring, shimmer) to tape delays, chorus, flanging, and dynamics processors modeled after the 1176, LA-2A, Neve 33609, SSL G Bus, Fairchild 670, and Distressor.
        </p>
        <p>
          Currently active: plate reverb for depth, a vocal doubler/thickener for width, a sub-octave generator adding mid presence to the bass, and the three guitar amp sims. Six slots are free for session-specific effects.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ruled">
      <h3>Software</h3>
      <div class="grid-2 mt-sm">
        <div class="card">
          <span class="card__label">Channel Strip</span>
          <h4>IK Multimedia MixBox</h4>
          <p>70+ modules including models of the Black 76, White 2A, Model 670, and British EQ. Up to 8 rack slots per instance for building custom processing chains in the DAW.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="card__label">Amp Sim</span>
          <h4>IK Multimedia AmpliTube 5</h4>
          <p>Over 100 amps and cabs modeled after Fender, Marshall, Mesa, and Orange. Full signal chain when you want to go deeper than the Wing's built-in sims.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="card__label">Tone Modeling</span>
          <h4>IK Multimedia TONEX</h4>
          <p>AI-powered tone capture. Model your own gear or browse thousands of community captures. Drop any real amp tone into the DAW.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="card__label">Tape Emulation</span>
          <h4>T-RackS Tape Machine</h4>
          <p>Tascam 388 emulation for tape compression, harmonic saturation, and frequency shaping. Runs as an insert on every playback track with per-instrument settings.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</Base>
